# How to build from source

## Requirements

### Common requirements

In order to build linm, you need to install several components:

- A C compiler (C++11)
- [CMake](http://www.cmake.org) >= 2.10.0.

optional:
- [libz](http://www.zlib.net) >= 1.2
- [openssl](http://www.openssl.org) >= 1.0.0
- [libssh2](http://www.libssh2.org]) >= 1.4.0
- [source-highlight](https://www.gnu.org/software/src-highlite/) >= 3.1.8

